  "faq": {
    "title": "Quick Answers",
    "subtitle": "Everything you need to know to get started",
    "questions": [
      {
        "q": "Is it really free?",
        "a": "Yes, completely free for citizens. Your local government covers the costs because they want to hear from you."
      },
      {
        "q": "How fast are issues fixed?",
        "a": "Most issues are addressed within 5-10 business days. Emergency issues like broken streetlights get priority."
      },
      {
        "q": "Can I stay anonymous?",
        "a": "Absolutely. You can report any issue without providing your name or contact information."
      },
      {
        "q": "What kinds of issues can I report?",
        "a": "Potholes, broken lights, graffiti, sidewalk issues, park maintenance, and more. If it affects your community, report it."
      },
      {
        "q": "Do I need to create an account?",
        "a": "No account needed for basic reporting. Create one only if you want to track your reports and get updates."
      },
      {
        "q": "Is my location shared?",
        "a": "Only the issue location is shared with city officials. Your personal location and identity remain private."
      }
    ]
  },
